title: Zoo golden gate — scoring: visit/feed awards, already-fed
story: friendly-zoo
description: Scoring as behavior-parity proof (AC-2 scoring category):
  room visits award 5 each (Petting Zoo, Aviary), feed-the-goats awards 10,
  petting awards nothing, and the already-fed refusal leaves the score
  unchanged. Authored against the TS story 2026-07-11, then frozen;
  max-score assertions revised 100 → 85 in Phase C P5 (gate-delta audit
  Entry 1, David sign-off 2026-07-12).

  Wording revised again 2026-07-24 (ADR-260 D3/D4): the zoo declares
  `use scoring` with no `ranks` block, so SCORE now answers `score_display`
  — "scored N out of a possible 85" — where it used to answer
  `score_with_rank` with a percentage-band rank stdlib invented. That free
  rank is deleted; a story that wants one writes a ladder. This transcript
  is therefore also the coverage for ADR-261 acceptance #4: scoring on, no
  ladder, a score and no rank.

---

> score
[OK: contains "scored 0 out of a possible 85"]

> south
[OK: contains "Main Path"]

> east
[OK: contains "Petting Zoo"]

# The Petting Zoo visit awarded +5; petting itself awards nothing
> pet goats
[OK: contains "bleats happily"]

> score
[OK: contains "scored 5 out of a possible 85"]

